index.js
Simple Discord queue bot with FCFS slots.

Features:
- Admin starts a queue with /startqueue
- Players click buttons to claim or release slots
- Max 2 slots per player
- A player cannot claim the same slot as their previous session slot
- Normal slots use /pick to assign 1 Pokemon
- Choice slots use /choosegroup and do not use /pick
- Valid Pokemon names only
- Banned Pokemon names are blocked
- FCFS priority is enforced across normal slots and choice slots
- If a Pokemon overlaps with an earlier claimed slot or choice group, the earlier claimant keeps it
- Reserve slots are used to generate the Reserves list and N!cl remove list
- /finish and /endqueue post the final summary

Requirements:
npm install discord.js better-sqlite3 dotenv

.env file:
DISCORD_TOKEN=your_bot_token
CLIENT_ID=your_application_client_id
GUILD_ID=your_test_server_id

validPokemon.js
List of all valid Pokemon names which can be picked.

choiceGroups.js
List of choice groups and the Pokemon in each group.

Admin commands: (People with ManageGuild / Manage Server permissions)
/startqueue
/endqueue
/finish
/adminremove

Public commands:
button claim/release
/choosegroup
/pick
/withdraw